    "Background": {
      "text": "Identification: Brown gray with white spots forming a longitudinal band on the dorsal abdomen and a red-brown brush of hair on the chelicerae. Large in size (4.5-6cm) with 4-5mm fangs.\nThey do not form webs, but rather are mobile nocturnal hunters\namong the largest and most aggressive spiders in South AmericaHabitat restricted to South America, largely Brazil, Argentina, and Uruguay.\nGenus: Phoneutria\nThe best-known representative is P. nigriventer, the Brazilian Wandering Spider",
      "subsections": {
        "Venom": {
          "text": "A complex mixture of polypeptide components. Neurotoxicity is the most clinically relevant.\nHistamine and other components potentiate localized swelling and vascular permeability\nSeveral neurotoxic components that activate sodium channels, potentiating action potentials and causing uncontrolled muscle contractions.",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
